\section{Conclusion}
The Hamiltonian Crystal framework provides a unified explanation for both proton stability and the nucleon spin composition. Portal couplings to dark-sector Fock modes naturally suppress proton decay while redistributing spin contributions between quarks, gluons, and vacuum modes. The framework yields concrete, testable predictions for proton lifetime, spin fraction, and correlated dark-sector signals, enabling falsifiable experimental tests.

